{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Push & Notify PR",
  "description": "Manually triggered: pushes uncommitted work to the feature branch, posts a status comment on the PR, requests review from master-agent, and starts PR monitoring.",
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Before finishing, check if there is any uncommitted or unpushed work:\n\n1. Run `git status` — if there are staged or unstaged changes, commit them with a conventional commit message and push to the current branch.\n2. Run `git log @{upstream}..HEAD 2>/dev/null || git log origin/$(git branch --show-current)..HEAD` — if there are unpushed commits, push them.\n3. Do NOT push to main directly. Only push to feature branches.\n4. If you were working on a feature branch with a GitHub PR, post a status update AND review request comment on the PR using the GitHub MCP server. Use this format:\n\n```\n**[emoji] [Agent Name]** — Ready for Review\n\n[What was accomplished in this session]\n[What remains to be done, if anything]\n[Current quality signal: 🟢/🟡/🔴]\n\n@master-agent — requesting code review.\n```\n\nThis signals the master-agent to begin the CR process.\n\n5. After posting your 'Ready for Review' comment, the PR monitoring system will automatically start checking for feedback. You don't need to manually poll — the system will invoke you when new reviews arrive. The monitoring happens via the `monitor-pr-after-ready.kiro.hook` which uses the `pr-monitor-skill.js` to poll GitHub API every 1-2 minutes."
  }
}